    summary: "Jagex will launch RuneScape: Dragonwilds in the Asia-Pacific region later this year, marking its most significant international expansion. The game will be localized in Simplified Chinese, Japanese, and Korean to connect with local player communities.",
    body: "Jagex will launch RuneScape: Dragonwilds in the Asia-Pacific (APAC) region later this year. The developer considers this its most significant international expansion to date.\n\nThe launch will feature localizations in Simplified Chinese, Japanese, and Korean. Jagex CEO Jon Bellamy emphasized the importance of connecting with these passionate player communities. He said, \"Launching in their native languages is not just a translation exercise.\"\n\nAPAC represents a substantial gaming market, with a significant interest in the survival crafting genre. Jagex aims to establish RuneScape as a global franchise, ensuring that the game aligns with regional preferences. Bellamy noted that RuneScape: Dragonwilds combines deep skilling systems, cooperative play, and rich world-building, making it appealing to these audiences.\n\nRuneScape: Dragonwilds began early access on Steam in April 2025 and expanded to Latin America in September with Portuguese and Spanish localizations. Earlier this year, Jagex SVP James Dobrowski outlined big plans for 2026, marking it as their most ambitious year yet.",
