    summary: "Faker and Gumayusi are pursuing legal action against anonymous internet users for defamation due to increased criticism and personal attacks in the South Korean League of Legends esports scene. Their agency, FANABLE, highlights the extent of toxicity among fans and players.",
    body: "Esports is full of passionate fans and players, so you\u2019re bound to come across heated debates and frustrated takes. In South Korea, where League of Legends esports is even more mainstream, that toxicity has become too much for FANABLE, the agency that represents Lee \u201cFaker\u201d Sang-hyeok and Park \u201cGumayusi\u201d Ji-soo.\n\nFaker and Gumayusi announced they are taking legal action against anonymous internet users for defamation. Both players have faced harsh criticism and personal attacks, which has surged following disappointing tournament performances. The toxicity of online comments has overwhelmed them.\n\nFANABLE stated that their commitment is to protect their clients from harmful online behavior. The agency aims to address the issues surrounding cyberbullying in the competitive gaming community. Legal action is seen as a necessary step to deter future abuse.\n\nThe situation reflects a larger issue affecting many gamers and streamers who are subjected to relentless negativity online. Fans must consider the impact of their words and actions, especially on prominent figures in the esports scene. \n\nAs esports continues to grow, addressing toxicity will be critical for the industry\u2019s health and the well-being of its stars. Less hostility could foster a better environment for players and fans alike.",
