    summary: "Players must master combat and puzzle-solving while navigating a lunar environment, utilizing Hugh's futuristic weapons and Diana's hacking abilities. The dual character control introduces a unique dynamic that challenges both mental agility and reflexes.",
    body: "tages for players who were willing to experiment and think outside the box.\"\n\nAs players navigate the eerie lunar environment, mastering both combat and puzzle-solving will be crucial. Hugh uses an array of futuristic weapons against artificially intelligent foes while Diana provides vital abilities to hack into enemies' systems. This dual character control creates a unique game dynamic, presenting challenges that require both mental agility and quick reflexes.\n\nThe development team faced a significant hurdle with the potential for repetitiveness in gameplay. The challenge was to ensure players remained engaged as they cycled through action sequences and puzzle-solving mechanics. By integrating these elements, Pragmata aims to keep the gameplay fresh and dynamic, pushing players to adapt their strategies frequently.\n\nIn blending puzzle-solving and action, Pragmata distinguishes itself from traditional third-person shooters. The innovative approach not only showcases Capcom's commitment to diversifying its game library but also presents a fascinating new entry into the genre. As excitement builds for its release this month, many are eager to see how this blend of tactics and visceral action will resonate with players.",
