    summary: "UK games studios are shifting their focus toward PC development, with 46 percent of studios prioritizing it from May 2024 to September 2025. Mobile development's share decreased from 33 percent to 31.6 percent, accompanied by a drop in related industry jobs from 19 percent to 17.9 percent.",
    body: "UK games studios are increasingly prioritizing PC development over mobile platforms, according to new data from trade body TIGA. Between May 2024 and September 2025, 46 percent of studios reported PC as their main focus, with 56 percent of start-ups also targeting this platform.\n\nMobile development's share declined from 33 percent to 31.6 percent during the same period. The number of industry jobs related to mobile fell from 19 percent to 17.9 percent, highlighting a shift in focus. In contrast, console games grew to represent 50 percent of industry jobs despite a slight reduction in console studio headcount.\n\nTIGA CEO Richard Wilson emphasized the resilience of PC and console development in the face of challenging market conditions. He noted that while the sector faces the \u201cmost severe downturn on record,\u201d PC remains the leading platform, and console production still employs a significant workforce.\n\nThe overall UK development sector has experienced a net loss of 1,537 jobs \u2014 a 4.5 percent annualized decrease. Wilson warned that without swift policy intervention, the UK risks losing skilled talent to better-supported international markets.",
