    body: "Gossip Harbor reached a significant milestone in March, surpassing $100 million in in-app purchase earnings for the first time. This marks a substantial increase from February\u2019s total of $82.5 million. Its continued revenue growth has it positioned to overtake Royal Match, which also performed well last month with just over $100 million.\n\nHonor of Kings maintained its top position despite a significant revenue drop to approximately $133 million, down from around $150 million in February. LastWar: Survival held the second spot, grossing about $125 million, a consistent figure since it crossed the $120 million threshold in August 2024.\n\nWhiteout Survival gained momentum, climbing to third place with earnings over $112 million, while PUBG Mobile saw a decline to around $110 million after peaking above $129 million in February. Royal Match rebounded from a February low, rejoining the ranks of top earners.\n\nRoblox's earnings improved to roughly $95 million, recovering from a low of about $80 million in February. However, its revenue is still below its typical summer highs of $150 million. Candy Crush Saga returned to its usual range with about $90 million, while Monopoly Go continued its troubling trend, earning approximately $89 million in March, a notable drop from January\u2019s $128 million.\n\nThe bottom half of the top 20 featured consistent performers such as Coin Master with around $55.7 million and Pok\u00e9mon Go with $46 million. Brawl Stars, from Supercell, rounded out the top 20 with about $34 million, reflecting ongoing challenges to maintain player engagement and revenue growth.",
